	h2 Events
	dl
		dt: dfn Event
		dd
			p.intro Our goal is to assign probability to certain #[b events]. #[span.example.main we would like to know the probability that the outcome of rolling a fair die is an even number. In this case, our event is the set #[+m E=\{2, 4, 6\}]. If the result of our random experiment belongs to the set #[+m E], we say that the event #[+m E] has occurred].
			p A subset of the sample space and to which we want to assign a probability #[eg a collection of possible outcomes]. 
				| #[br]If #[+m A] and #[+m B] are events, then #[+m A \cup B] and #[+m A \cap B] are also events.
			ul(title="Set operations")
				li: p #[dfn Union #[+m A \cup B]] - Event #[+m A \cup B] occurs if #[+m A] #[strong or] #[+m B] occur. Similarly #[+m({'A_1, A_2,\\cdots, A_n': 'events'}) A_1 \cup A_2 \cup A_3 \cdots \cup A_n] occurs if #[strong at least] one of #[+m A_1, A_2,\cdots, A_n] occurs.
				li: p #[dfn Intersection #[+m A \cap B]] - Event #[+m A \cap B] occurs if #[+m A] #[strong and] #[+m B] occur. Similarly #[+m({'A_1, A_2,\\cdots, A_n': 'events'}) A_1 \cap A_2 \cap A_3 \cdots \cap A_n] occurs if #[strong all of] #[+m A_1, A_2,\cdots, A_n] occurs.

